project.p:
    The time, T, it takes for the Moon to eclipse the Sun totally is given (in minutes) by the formula
    T=\frac{1}{v}\left(\frac{rD}{R}-d \right) where d is the diameter of the Moon, D is the diameter of the Sun, r is the distance from the Earth to the Moon, R is the distance from the Earth to the Sun, and v is the speed of the Moon.



Solve the formula for v in terms of the other variables.


It takes 2.68 minutes for the Moon to eclipse the Sun. Calculate the speed of the Moon given the following values:

            d = 3.48 × 103 \text{ km}\amp\amp D = 1.41 × 106 \text{ km}
            r = 3.82 × 105 \text{ km} \amp\amp R = 1.48 × 108 \text{ km}
